   411→// InjectItem allows injecting a single Item at the beginning of the token stream
   412→// consumed by the generated parser.
   413→// This allows having multiple start symbols as described in
   414→// https://www.gnu.org/software/bison/manual/html_node/Multiple-start_002dsymbols.html .
   415→// Only the Lex function used by the generated parser is affected by this injected Item.
   416→// Trying to inject when a previously injected Item has not yet been consumed will panic.
   417→// Only Item types that are supposed to be used as start symbols are allowed as an argument.
   418→func (p *parser) InjectItem(typ ItemType) {
